## Design decisions and coverage rationale

| # | Test class | What it validates |
|---|-----------|-------------------|
| 1 | `TestSuccessfulPatientCreation` | Happy-path: object type, status, field values, persistence, UUID, timestamp, creating-clinician tracking |
| 2 | `TestPermissionDenial` | Read-only clinician, admin, receptionist, inactive account, unauthenticated (`None`) — all must raise `AuthorizationError` and must **not** call `repo.save` |
| 3 | `TestMissingMandatoryFields` | Parametrised over every mandatory field; checks exception type, field name in message, no persistence; also tests fully empty and `None` payloads and bulk-missing error reporting |
| 4 | `TestDemographicFieldValidation` | NHS number (Luhn), date-of-birth (future/past/type), gender enum, name length, nested address, email, phone |
| 5 | `TestDuplicateAndConflictingState` | NHS number already exists → `DuplicateResourceError`; existing record referenced in error; no overwrite |
| 6 | `TestConflictingStateTransitions` | Deceased, merged, deleted record with the same NHS number must be rejected (`InvalidStateTransitionError` or `DuplicateResourceError`); no save |
| 7 | `TestIdempotencyAndConcurrency` | Sequential duplicate rejected; idempotency-key replay returns original object with a single `save` call |
| 8 | `TestAuditTrail` | Success, permission-denied, and validation-failed paths each emit exactly one structured audit event with the correct `action` and `actor_id` |
| 9 | `TestAPILayer` | HTTP status codes 201, 400, 401, 403, 409; error body contains field name; success body contains `id` |

